Candida auris went from unknown to global health threat in 10 short years. How did this happen? We trace the history of this emerging fungal pathogen in our latest Bugs & Drugs article on asm.org.
.
3 factors make C. auris an important and dangerous pathogen:
1. It is HIGHLY drug resistant.
2. It is easily spread.
3. It is commonly misidentified.
.
What are the best practices for diagnosing C. auris infection? How should highly drug-resistant C. auris infections be treated? We summarize the latest research in our Bugs & Drugs article. Find it on asm.org or find a direct link on our Facebook page at Facebook.com/asmfan.
.

#Hygiene plays a pivotal role in reducing the incidence of infections, thereby minimizing the need for #antibiotics, #antimicrobials and mitigating the emergence of #antimicrobialresistant (#AMR) microbes. Proper handwashing, safe food handling, and oral hygiene disrupt microbial transmission pathways, preventing opportunistic infections that often necessitate antibiotic and antimicrobial use. Lower antibiotic exposure exerts less selective pressure on bacterial populations, reducing the likelihood of #resistance development.

latestPosts.caption: #Hygiene plays a pivotal role in reducing the incidence of infections, thereby minimizing the need for #antibiotics, #antimicrobials and mitigating the emergence of #antimicrobialresistant (#AMR) microbes. Proper handwashing, safe food handling, and oral hygiene disrupt microbial transmission pathways, preventing opportunistic infections that often necessitate antibiotic and antimicrobial use. Lower antibiotic exposure exerts less selective pressure on bacterial populations, reducing the likelihood of #resistance development.

#NewStudy üì¢ Microplastics offer a platform for antimicrobial-resistant (AMR) and pathogenic bacteria, responsible for diseases in both humans and animals. The study, led by PhD researcher Emily Stevenson (@emilystevensonbg) (hosted at PML and the University of Exeter (@uniofexeter / @exetermarine), reveals for the first time, that the type of particle affects colonization, enrichment and spread of both #AMR and pathogenic bacteria. Please also check out Emily's Community Interest Company Beach Guardian (@beachguardian) which aims to empower communities against plastic waste.
